title: For Sale:  Spyderco
postcontent: This is a collectors piece! Spyderco Spyderfly.  The spyderfly infuses traditional bali-song knife elements with innovative Spyderco design.  The blade is VG-10 that is sharpened on one side only. The spyderfly utilizes a dual-tang-pin-design. Large tang pins give a bigger contact area with the handles and are, therefore, stronger and more durable. If you squeeze hard you can just barely get them to meet. The harder you squeeze, the stronger an open bali-song is... until the handles touch. So by using a large tang pin and spacing the handles apart, spyderco allows you to squeeze hard and get a strong knife as a result. This is important because the spyderfly cannot be locked open. The latch only works to lock the knife closed. This may skirt legal restrictions on locking knives in some areas. However the spyderfly can lock shut making it a very safe knife to carry. In fact, the latch is part of  what makes the spyderfly unique. It's spring loaded. Just squeeze the handles and the latch springs open. The blade is a modified spearpoint. Spyderco hardens the blade to 59-60 rockwell hardness. The blade is made from 1/8" thick VG-10 steel. The edge is flat ground and very sharp. the blade has a very nice brushed finish. The blade is very symetrical. Beautiful piece to have and not easily found in new, mint condition in original box

I also replaced a few parts with polished nickel parts, mainly for looks, the mag release and the safety switch. I also have a nickel slide lock and a Nickel Trigger but haven't put it on yet. I have all the stock parts too that will come with the gun as well as the hard plastic Bersa gun case and all original paperwork. This gun also has a key lock for the trigger which is pretty cool, makes it very simple to lock the trigger so the gun can be stored safely.I also have extra mags for the gun, I will include an extra one, and will sell more of them if you want more, as well as ammo too.Will also include a nice custom holster. The free one is a "sticky" holster that you put the gun in and tuck the holster into you pants for easy concealment. It's my favorite kind of concealing holster. The other holster I have is a Fobus paddle holster to wear the gun on your hip by just sliding The "paddle" inside you pants along your hip.. It's custom fit for this gun and is a very good quality, it's also the most comfortable holster you will find, it doesn't pull down on your belt or move around while you're walking. I'll include it for an extra $15 which is way less than you can buy one for.

postcontent: https://www.inlanderarms.com/products/comboInlander Arms has CA Compliance kits for 80% handguns.$249.99https://www.inlanderarms.com/products/comboPatent PendingFeatured on The Firearm Bloghttp://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2017/02/20/bolt-action-glock-california/ Are you building pistols from 80%? Use our slide conversion to help you stay legal by building them as a dimensionally compliant single shot bolt action. The https://www.inlanderarms.com/products/easy-bolt-retrofit-system Easy Bolt™ is CNC machined (made in California) from 6061 Aluminum. The Easy Bolt™ is compatible with the PF940, PF940C, PF940SC, Glockstore SS80 (Glock 43), Sig P320 Compact, and more!We are now offering a more universal option for your CA compliant 80% handgun builds: EASY BOLT + UNIVERSAL 9MM TO .25ACP BARREL INSERT$249.99Now you can buy one kit that will allow you to build/transfer the following handguns (and possibly future polymer80 offerings):PF940 (Glock 17)PF940C (Glock 19)PF940SC (Glock 26)Glockstore SS80 (Glock 43)Sig P320 CompactLone Wolf Timberwolf (Glock 17)Lone Wolf Timberwolf (Glock 19)https://www.inlanderarms.com/products/comboOur Barrel Inserts are Machined from Stainless Steel and drop in to any SAAMI spec 9mm barrel. Use your compliance kit for a variety of builds!Video of the prototype installed on a Glock 17:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f586VbyE5nIFAQQ: Do I really need to build my 80% handgun this way to be legal?A: If you are a California resident and intend to build here, yes http://www.calguns.net/calgunforum/showthread.php?t=896755 (AB 1964). If you plan on registering your gun, CA DOJ is asking for proof (pictures) of how it was built legally.Starting July 2018, all 80% builds will have to go through the registration process with CA DOJ CA Penal Code prohibits building "unsafe" handguns like the Polymer80 PF940C except:(b) Article 4 (commencing with Section 31900) and Article 5 (commencing with Section 32000) shall not apply to a single-shot pistol with a break top or bolt action and a barrel length of not less than six inches and that has an overall length of at least 10½ inches when the handle, frame or receiver, and barrel are assembled.Q: How is this better than a complete upper/slide replacement?A: The Easy Bolt was designed to be as safe and cost effective as possible. You are converting a Glock slide without having to modify any of the critical (and proven) slide components that interact with the components on the frame. You can also test your completed pistol frame (fitting the rails and testing the trigger) without breaking the law.Q: Can I use this to do SSE2 transfers of pistols such as the Lone Wolf Timberwolf Glock frames?A: The way AB 1964 amended the single shot exemption to the Handgun Roster, you can no longer SSE handguns that were previously semi auto (such as a Gen 4 Glock 19). We developed this solution for 80% builds, but it might be possible to SSE a Timberwolf frame if it is truly a virgin frame. We do not explicitly advise anyone to attempt this without first consulting with an attorney and have the blessing from Lone Wolf or another FFL that is comfortable doing the transfer. View the discussion on this topic http://www.calguns.net/calgunforum/showthread.php?t=1301726Q: How do I load it when it's single shot?A: You will load a cartridge directly into the breech from the top. You must be careful not to damage your extractor when loading this way. Slamming the breech shut will likely damage your extractor. If you are worried about this happening, it is best to remove the extractor when you convert your slide. Leave the extractor in at your own risk.Q: Do I need to modify the magazine release to make my build single shot?A: Using the .25ACP Barrel Insert renders your slide a single shot. There is no way to magazine-feed in this configuration.
